Make: The database contain few cars not sold in Europe, due of my personal research and due of requests from non-European users.
European users are advised to filter column "Sold in Europe" and delete rows marked with "NO".
Western European users can further delete rows marked with "Only Russia", "Eastern Europe", etc.
Eastern European users can further delete what is marked as "Only UK" but are advised to not, because some used cars from UK are now on the roads of Eastern Europe.
Advice for webdesigners and software developers

Do you need car data rows only and want to get rid of Make header rows? Select entire table, Tools, Auto filter, click Filter box of Model name column, select Blanks, select all rows, right click, delete.
Do you want production start and end year to be in separate columns? Select Year column and go in Tools menu > Text to columns, use hyphen as delimiter

You may want to delete columns A, B and C, which are there mostly for statistical purposes, to count how many model platforms are included in database, also to sort models by class and years, also to create a simple list for showing on website as "List of car models included in the FULL database".

For making drop-down lists DO NOT use column H because model names are not unique and sometimes are not descriptive enough, for example Volkswagen Golf IV have 6 rows with identical name "Golf 1.9 TDI" due of having 6 different power versions. Use column I instead (model name + cm³ + horsepower + years), this column can also be used to create unique ID.
